Analysis of Main Target Image
1) Overall Count and Layers

• Left‐Hand Structure (2 layers, 3 total blocks):  
   – Layer 1: Two red curved “wave” blocks side by side  
   – Layer 2: One blue cube centered atop those two red blocks  

• Right‐Hand “Temple” Structure (5 layers, 7 total blocks):  
   – Layer 1: One yellow rectangular block (horizontal)  
   – Layer 2: Two orange cylinders standing upright, side by side  
   – Layer 3: One yellow rectangular block (horizontal)  
   – Layer 4: One red arch block  
   – Layer 5: Two orange triangular blocks forming a peaked roof  

2) Selecting Blocks from Dictionary

Matching each piece exactly (including color and orientation) yields these required indices:

• Left Structure  
   – Two red “wave” blocks: dictionary index 3 (used twice)  
   – Blue cube: dictionary index 6  

• Right Structure  
   – Yellow rectangles (horizontal): dictionary index 9 (used twice)  
   – Orange cylinders (vertical): dictionary index 12 (used twice)  
   – Red arch (opening downward, wide left–right): dictionary index 1  
   – Orange triangular roof pieces (left and right): dictionary indices 14 and 15  

Hence the full set of needed blocks (by index) is:
{1, 3, 3, 6, 9, 9, 12, 12, 14, 15}.

3) Assembly Order

A possible step‐by‐step sequence:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 3
  Step2: Move block with index 3
  Step3: Move block with index 6
  Step4: Move block with index 9
  Step5: Move block with index 12
  Step6: Move block with index 12
  Step7: Move block with index 9
  Step8: Move block with index 1
  Step9: Move block with index 14
  Step10: Move block with index 15
}
